<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Is there any way the kill count can be rejiggered to display the kill count in order of monster badness? AFAICT without code diving, the current list is formed in order of the first creature you kill of a particular type.  <p>
Toggling back and forth between the two types of lists would be nice. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: According to my observations, the kill count is actually ordered by monster id. That's why dragon worms and water critters always end up in the tail of the list. They were late additions and got big ids. I've also been thinking the list could be arranged better... 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: Really? Thanks, I didn't know that. I've got a bunch of dragonworms at the tail of my list, and the very last 4 are White Balrog, Golgarach, water hounds, and Emperor Mimic. 
</p>
